<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,327]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,369,151,177]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Larval hosts:</emphasis>
Larvae feed on forest trees including linden (
<taxonomicName box="[934,1036,152,178]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Tilia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[934,990,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Tilia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1051,1167,152,178]" family="Tiliaceae" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="family">Tiliaceae</taxonomicName>
), walnut (
<taxonomicName box="[1290,1430,152,178]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" genus="Juglans" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1290,1384,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Juglans</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,312,189,215]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Juglandaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Crumb, E. S." box="[337,493,189,215]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 356" refId="ref30510" refString="Crumb, E. S. (1956) The larvae of the Phalaenidae. U. S. Department of Agriculture Technical Bulletin, 1135, 1 - 356." type="journal article" year="1956">Crumb 1956</bibRefCitation>
), European white birch (
<taxonomicName authority="Roth" authorityName="Roth" box="[794,1046,189,215]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pendula">
<emphasis box="[794,976,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Betula pendula</emphasis>
Roth
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S.F.Gray" authorityYear="1822" box="[1059,1195,189,215]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
), butternut (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" genus="Juglans" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cinerea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Juglans cinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName box="[296,468,226,252]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Juglandaceae</taxonomicName>
), white ash (
<taxonomicName box="[631,885,226,251]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Oleaceae" genus="Fraxinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis box="[631,885,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fraxinus americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Hoffmannsegg &amp; Link" authorityYear="1809" box="[939,1058,226,252]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Oleaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Oleaceae</taxonomicName>
), white oak (
<taxonomicName box="[1224,1392,226,251]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[1224,1392,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Quercus alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dumortier" authorityYear="1829" box="[151,269,264,290]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
), bur oak (
<taxonomicName authority="Michx." authorityName="Michx." box="[402,685,264,290]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrocarpa">
<emphasis box="[402,586,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Q. macrocarpa</emphasis>
Michx.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dumortier" authorityYear="1829" box="[699,814,264,290]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Prentice, R. M." box="[839,1014,264,290]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="75 - 281" refId="ref30996" refString="Prentice, R. M. (1962) Forest Lepidoptera of Canada. Volume 2. Nycteolidae, Noctuida, Notodontidae, Liparidae. Canadian Department of Forestry Bulletin, 128, 75 - 281." type="journal article" year="1962">Prentice 1962</bibRefCitation>
), and maple (
<taxonomicName box="[1182,1285,264,290]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Acer" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1182,1239,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Acer</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1300,1428,264,290]" family="Aceraceae" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="family">Aceraceae</taxonomicName>
) (Kimball 1965). The larva is illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, D. L." box="[647,827,301,327]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref31242" refString="Wagner, D. L. (2005) Caterpillars of Eastern North America. Princeton University Press, Princeton, New Jersey, 512 pp." type="book" year="2005">Wagner (2005)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
